Package: ialctl
Version: 6.30.3-interactive-auto
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Diego Nardoni <diego@nardoni.com>
Description: IAL Infrastructure CLI v6.30.3 - Interactive Mode Auto-Start
 Revolutionary AWS Infrastructure deployment with infinite conversational memory
 and automatic interactive mode when no arguments provided.
 .
 v6.30.3 UX IMPROVEMENT:
 - ialctl (no args) now automatically starts interactive mode
 - No more usage message - direct conversation interface
 - Seamless user experience like Amazon Q
 - Natural language interaction by default
 .
 Command Behaviors:
 - ialctl → Interactive mode (automatic)
 - ialctl start → Deploy foundation infrastructure
 - ialctl configure → Configure settings
 - ialctl interactive → Interactive mode (explicit)
 - ialctl "command" → Direct execution
 .
 Memory Features (Preserved):
 - Infinite Memory (never forgets conversations or context)
 - DynamoDB + S3 Glacier persistence (cost: $0.15/user/month)
 - Bedrock Embeddings for semantic search
 - Smart context retrieval across sessions
 - Amazon Q-like interactive experience
 - Automatic memory resource deployment via ialctl start
 - Memory commands: /stats, /history, /forget
 - Local cache fallback (works offline)
 .
 Infrastructure Features (Preserved):
 - Foundation Bootstrap: ialctl start → deploys 45+ resources
 - Smart Routing: conversation vs infrastructure detection
 - GitHub as source of truth
 - YAML template generation with cost guardrails
 - Complete audit trail and governance
 - MCP configuration properly embedded
 .
 v6.30.3 provides the most natural user experience with
 automatic interactive mode and infinite conversational memory.
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8), python3-pip, python3-boto3
Homepage: https://github.com/Diego-Nardoni/ial-infrastructure
